896259406.text: "Phosphorylation of raptor and TSC2, as downstream effectors of the ROS-AMPK axis, reduced mTORC1 activity since i) raptor phosphorylation at Ser-722 and Ser-792 can promote its binding to 14-3-3, which would attenuate the Ser Thr kinase function of mTOR [XREF_BIBR]; and ii) stimulatory phosphorylation of TSC2 at Ser 1387 can enhance the TSC2 and TSC1 tuberous sclerosis complex activity, which is a negative regulator of mTORC1 [XREF_BIBR]."
